Introduction

We are creating a 2D superhero sidescroll/base defense game.  The playable character will destroy enemies as they try to collapse upon a base.  
Functional Requirements

Menu (start, options, quit)
?Multiple Levels
?Different characters
?Different abilities/speeds
High score list
Game modes
Items/Powerups
Shield
Additional Superpowers
Screen Clear
Interactive Environment
Some obstacles can be broken
Moving platforms
Music/sounds
Taken from other games or free repositories
Non-Functional Requirements

Not too cpu-heavy
Programmed in Java
Kept up to date with future versions
30 Fps
System Evolution

Will support upcoming Java versions.
Glossary

SideScroller - a video game in which the gameplay action is viewed from a side-view camera angle, and the onscreen characters generally move from the left side of the screen to the right to meet an objective.
Fps - frames per second
Powerup - objects that instantly benefit or add extra abilities to the game character.

